This article discusses President Donald J. Trump's opposition to the socialist model of healthcare, particularly Medicare-for-All. The article claims that this model would ration care, restrict access, lower quality, and result in long wait times for treatments. President Trump emphasizes his belief in freedom, choice, and the highest standard of care. He also criticizes the lies surrounding Obamacare and warns that Medicare-for-All would endanger seniors by restricting their benefits and preventing them from purchasing supplemental insurance. The article highlights President Trump's efforts to expand healthcare choice while criticizing Congressional Democrats for attempting to control every aspect of healthcare. Overall, the article argues against the implementation of Medicare-for-All and supports President Trump's stance on healthcare.